<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="431" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1518,1977]" pageId="1" pageNumber="431">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,1698,1724]" pageId="1" pageNumber="431">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The male of 
<taxonomicName authority="Jocqué &amp; Jocque &amp; Mbende, 2022" authorityName="Jocqué &amp; Jocque &amp; Mbende" authorityYear="2022" box="[473,698,1699,1725]" class="Arachnida" family="Telemidae" genus="Cangoderces" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="431" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wewef" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[473,698,1699,1725]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="431">Cangoderces wewef</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[705,769,1699,1725]" pageId="1" pageNumber="431">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[705,769,1699,1725]" pageId="1" pageNumber="431" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is characterized by the shape of the bulbus with a deep triangular dorsal indentation absent in other species of the genus and by the shape of the embolus and the appendages at its base. The female is characterized by the fusiform shape of the sclerotized spermatheca which has a different shape in other species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="431" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1518,1977]" pageId="1" pageNumber="431">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1843,1869]" pageId="1" pageNumber="431">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species name is an arbitrary combination of letters containing twice W and F; it is a noun in apposition and refers to the World Wildlife Fund and its contribution to the conservation of biodiversity in this region.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="435" pageId="1" pageNumber="431" type="description">
