<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1383,1662]" pageId="3" pageNumber="433">
Color (
<figureCitation box="[280,423,1383,1409]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1901,1925]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,179,1875]" captionTargetId="figure-18@2.[151,1436,179,1875]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Cangoderces wewef sp. n. A–B: Holotype male; C–D: Paratype female (247534). A. Habitus, dorsal view. B. do., ventral view. C. Habitus, dorsal view. D. do., ventral view. Scale bars: A–B = 200 μm; C–D: 500 μm." pageId="3" pageNumber="433">Figs. 1 A, B</figureCitation>
): Carapace yellow with dark brown mottling on broad lateral band and star shaped patch around fovea; chelicerae and legs yellow; sternum yellow suffused with black; abdomen: dorsum pale grey with faint paler pattern, sides and venter white with dark pattern around spinnerets.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1383,1662]" box="[199,750,1491,1518]" pageId="3" pageNumber="433">Fovea: length 0.09, anterior end 0.12 from AME.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1383,1662]" box="[199,1338,1527,1554]" pageId="3" pageNumber="433">AER straight from above, width 0.15. All eyes circular and with diameter about 0.02. PER 0.16 wide.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1383,1662]" box="[199,1241,1563,1590]" pageId="3" pageNumber="433">Leg spination: all P with one dorsal spine; TiI and TiII with one dorsal spine near the middle.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1383,1662]" box="[199,1110,1599,1626]" pageId="3" pageNumber="433">TiIV with transverse dorsal depressions, possibly accompanying Emerit’s glands.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1383,1662]" box="[199,571,1635,1662]" pageId="3" pageNumber="433">Legs measurements (see table 1).</paragraph>
