<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,151,573]" pageId="4" pageNumber="434">
Abdomen (
<figureCitation box="[324,451,151,177]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1901,1925]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,179,1875]" captionTargetId="figure-18@2.[151,1436,179,1875]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Cangoderces wewef sp. n. A–B: Holotype male; C–D: Paratype female (247534). A. Habitus, dorsal view. B. do., ventral view. C. Habitus, dorsal view. D. do., ventral view. Scale bars: A–B = 200 μm; C–D: 500 μm." pageId="4" pageNumber="434">Figs. 1A, B</figureCitation>
) with typical shape of male 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fage" authorityYear="1913" box="[762,883,151,177]" class="Arachnida" family="Telemidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="4" pageNumber="434" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Telemidae</taxonomicName>
: wider at the posterior end; with dorsal sclerotized pattern on pedicel; dispersed long setae on dorsum. Colulus well developed, pentagonal.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,151,573]" pageId="4" pageNumber="434">
Male palp: (
<figureCitation box="[335,467,223,249]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1277,1301]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1253]" captionTargetId="figure-22@3.[151,1436,181,1253]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Cangoderces wewef sp. n. Paratype male (247535).A. Tibia IV, dorsal view of central part with transverse grooves of Emerit’s glands. B. Male palp, dorsal view. C. do., retrolateral view. D. do., detail of previous. E: Embolus" pageId="4" pageNumber="434">Figs. 2B–D</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[479,550,223,249]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1899,1923]" captionTargetBox="[168,1436,909,1873]" captionTargetId="figure-221@4.[151,1436,907,1875]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Cangoderces wewef sp. n. Holotype male. A. Palp, retrolateral view. B. do. C. Palp, prolateral view. D. do. Scale bars: 100 μm. E: Embolus 100. E: Embolus; PTA: Prolateral Tubular Apophysis." pageId="4" pageNumber="434">3A–D</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[561,632,223,249]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1341,1365]" captionTargetBox="[155,1436,181,1310]" captionTargetId="figure-22@5.[151,1436,181,1317]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Cangoderces wewef sp. n. A–B: Paratype male (247535); C–D: Paratype female (247534). A. Male palp, retrolateral view. B. do.; slightly tilted towards frontal view; C. Endogyne, ventral view. D. Spinnerets and colulus, ventral view. Scale lines: 100 μm. E: Embolus; PTA: Prolateral Tubular Apophysis; ST: Spermatheca." pageId="4" pageNumber="434">4A, B</figureCitation>
): Cymbium long, slender and straight; bulbus large with deep dorsal indentation near centre; embolus inserted on retrolateral side broad, slightly widened towards downward pointing tip, its base with sharp excrescences (
<figureCitation box="[531,666,295,321]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1277,1301]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1253]" captionTargetId="figure-22@3.[151,1436,181,1253]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Cangoderces wewef sp. n. Paratype male (247535).A. Tibia IV, dorsal view of central part with transverse grooves of Emerit’s glands. B. Male palp, dorsal view. C. do., retrolateral view. D. do., detail of previous. E: Embolus" pageId="4" pageNumber="434">Figs. 2C, D</figureCitation>
); prolateral side of bulbus with tubular apophysis with membranous attachment.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,151,573]" box="[199,1114,366,393]" pageId="4" pageNumber="434">
Female 
<typeStatus box="[289,389,367,393]" pageId="4" pageNumber="434">paratype</typeStatus>
. Total length 1.14 Carapace length 0.41, width 0.35, height 0.22.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,151,573]" pageId="4" pageNumber="434">
Color (
<figureCitation box="[232,379,403,429]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1901,1925]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,179,1875]" captionTargetId="figure-18@2.[151,1436,179,1875]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Cangoderces wewef sp. n. A–B: Holotype male; C–D: Paratype female (247534). A. Habitus, dorsal view. B. do., ventral view. C. Habitus, dorsal view. D. do., ventral view. Scale bars: A–B = 200 μm; C–D: 500 μm." pageId="4" pageNumber="434">Figs. 1 C, D</figureCitation>
): Carapace brown, slightly suffused with black; no dark patch around fovea; sternum brown suffused with black; legs yellowish brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,151,573]" box="[199,666,475,501]" pageId="4" pageNumber="434">Fovea poorly developed. Eyes as in male.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,151,573]" box="[199,787,511,537]" pageId="4" pageNumber="434">Legs without spines. FIV strongly curved backward.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,151,573]" box="[199,561,547,573]" pageId="4" pageNumber="434">Leg measurements (see table 2).</paragraph>
