<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1483,1726]" pageId="5" pageNumber="435">
Abdomen oval, with few dispersed setae; colulus well developed, pentagonal. Anterior lateral spinnerets twosegmented, much longer than posterior lateral spinnerets which are provided with a row of aciniform gland spigots (cf. 
<bibRefCitation author="Murphy, J. A. &amp; Roberts, M. J." box="[196,481,1555,1582]" pageId="5" pageNumber="435" refId="ref3468" refString="Murphy, J. A. &amp; Roberts, M. J. (2015) Spider families of the world and their spinnerets. Vols. 1 &amp; 2. British Arachnological Society, York, xi + 552 pp." type="book" year="2015">Murphy &amp; Roberts, 2015</bibRefCitation>
) and very short posterior median spinnerets.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1483,1726]" pageId="5" pageNumber="435">
Endogyne (
<figureCitation box="[328,424,1591,1618]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1341,1365]" captionTargetBox="[155,1436,181,1310]" captionTargetId="figure-22@5.[151,1436,181,1317]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Cangoderces wewef sp. n. A–B: Paratype male (247535); C–D: Paratype female (247534). A. Male palp, retrolateral view. B. do.; slightly tilted towards frontal view; C. Endogyne, ventral view. D. Spinnerets and colulus, ventral view. Scale lines: 100 μm. E: Embolus; PTA: Prolateral Tubular Apophysis; ST: Spermatheca." pageId="5" pageNumber="435">Fig. 4 C</figureCitation>
): ventral view of outside a crescent shaped membranous area; internally with large sclerotized, fusiform spermatheca consisting of broad procurved part and complex central part directed forward.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="435" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1483,1726]" pageId="5" pageNumber="435">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,1663,1689]" pageId="5" pageNumber="435">Distribution.</emphasis>
Only known from 
<typeStatus box="[562,610,1664,1690]" pageId="5" pageNumber="435">type</typeStatus>
locality in 
<collectingCountry box="[734,853,1664,1690]" name="Democratic Republic of the Congo" pageId="5" pageNumber="435">DR Congo</collectingCountry>
close to Malebo, Mai-Ndombe Province, 
<collectingCountry box="[1317,1437,1664,1690]" name="Democratic Republic of the Congo" pageId="5" pageNumber="435">DR Congo</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation box="[159,228,1699,1726]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1404,1428]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1380]" captionTargetId="figure-18@6.[151,1435,181,1380]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 5. Distribution of Cangoderces in Africa; red symbol: Cangoderces wewef n. sp., black symbols: other species." pageId="5" pageNumber="435">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
